Patch Set 6: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(3 inline comments)

Couple comments inline. I think this patch needs to be tweaked a little because it appears that an HTTPGone will always be raised if the image doesn't exist during an image upload request. It should only be an HTTPGone if the data successfully uploads and when trying to set the image to active it errors because the image no longer exists.

Patch Set 6: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(2 inline comments)

TBH I don't think the UTs within this patch can verify the change correctness since there are a lot of fakes, we need a functional test case to verity the real scenario which can trigger the bug situation. But I agree it will not be easy, and I think it's not a blocker to me.
